<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>blindspot — Knowledge Resilience Report</title>
<style>
:root {
  --bg: #fafbfc;
  --fg: #0f172a;
  --muted: #64748b;
  --border: #e2e8f0;
  --card: #ffffff;
  --accent: #2563eb;
  --critical: #dc2626;
  --high: #d97706;
  --medium: #0891b2;
  --healthy: #16a34a;
}
* { box-sizing: border-box; }
body {
  margin: 0;
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--fg);
  font: 14px/1.5 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
}
.container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 64px; }
header { padding-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 32px; }
header h1 { margin: 0 0 4px; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
header .tagline { margin: 0 0 12px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 15px; }
header .meta { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; }
header .meta code { background: #f1f5f9; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; }
section { margin-bottom: 40px; }
h2 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
.group-title {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  margin: 48px 0 20px;
  padding-bottom: 10px;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
}
.group-title:first-of-type { margin-top: 24px; }
.cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
.card {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 16px;
}
.card .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.card .value { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 4px; }
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
th { text-align: left; font-weight: 500; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; padding: 12px 16px; background: #f8fafc; }
td { padding: 12px 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
td.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
td code, code.path { font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 13px; }
.badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; }
.badge.critical { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.badge.high { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.badge.medium { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.badge.healthy, .badge.low { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.empty { color: var(--muted); padding: 16px; text-align: center; background: var(--card); border: 1px dashed var(--border); border-radius: 8px; }
footer { margin-top: 48px; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; }
footer p { margin: 4px 0; }
.note { background: #fff7ed; border-left: 3px solid var(--high); padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 4px; color: #92400e; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.resilience { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 1fr) 2fr; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.resilience .overall { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; }
.resilience .overall .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.resilience .overall .score { font-size: 56px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; margin-top: 4px; letter-spacing: -0.03em; }
.resilience .overall .band { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; }
.resilience .subs { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
.resilience .sub { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px; border-left-width: 4px; border-left-style: solid; }
.resilience .sub .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.resilience .sub .value { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.band-strong { color: var(--healthy); border-left-color: var(--healthy); }
.band-moderate { color: var(--medium); border-left-color: var(--medium); }
.band-fragile { color: var(--high); border-left-color: var(--high); }
.band-critical { color: var(--critical); border-left-color: var(--critical); }
.resilience .summary { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin: 4px 2px 0; }
.letter-grade {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-left: 8px;
  padding: 2px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04);
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.letter-grade-sub {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-left: 6px;
  padding: 0 6px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.05);
  color: var(--muted);
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.sub.focus-here {
  outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
  outline-offset: -2px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1) inset;
}
.focus-tag {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-left: 6px;
  padding: 1px 6px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  font-size: 9px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  background: var(--accent);
  color: white;
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.profile-tag { margin: 12px 2px 0; font-size: 13px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.profile-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 3px 10px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
}
.profile-badge.profile-single-maintainer,
.profile-badge.profile-founder-led { background: #eef2ff; color: #4338ca; }
.profile-badge.profile-team { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.profile-badge.profile-multi-org { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.profile-badge.profile-doc-only { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.profile-badge.profile-unknown { background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06); color: var(--muted); }
.profile-note { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12.5px; }
.event-marker { display: inline-block; padding: 1px 8px; border-radius: 4px; background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; }
.executive-brief {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 18px 22px;
  margin-bottom: 28px;
}
.executive-brief .eyebrow {
  color: var(--accent);
  font-size: 11px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}
.executive-brief .overall-line {
  margin: 0 0 14px;
  font-size: 15px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.executive-brief .overall-tag {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 3px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}
.executive-brief .overall-tag.band-strong { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.executive-brief .overall-tag.band-moderate { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.executive-brief .overall-tag.band-fragile { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.executive-brief .overall-tag.band-critical { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.executive-brief .overall-text { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }
.executive-brief .risk-list-title {
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.executive-brief ol {
  margin: 0 0 14px;
  padding-left: 0;
  list-style: none;
  counter-reset: brief-risk;
}
.executive-brief ol li {
  counter-increment: brief-risk;
  padding: 6px 0;
  border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border);
  font-size: 14px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 8px;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.executive-brief ol li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.executive-brief ol li::before {
  content: counter(brief-risk) ".";
  color: var(--muted);
  font-weight: 700;
  min-width: 18px;
}
.executive-brief .risk-prio {
  font-size: 10px;
  padding: 2px 7px;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}
.executive-brief .risk-target { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12.5px; }
.executive-brief .risk-target code { font-size: 12px; }
.executive-brief .business-implication {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f0f9ff 0%, #ffffff 100%);
  border: 1px solid #bae6fd;
  border-radius: 6px;
  font-size: 13.5px;
  line-height: 1.55;
  color: #1e293b;
}
.executive-brief .bi-eyebrow {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-right: 8px;
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  color: var(--accent);
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.executive-brief .patterns-summary { margin: 0 0 12px; font-size: 13.5px; }
.pattern-summary-tag {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 3px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  margin-right: 6px;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
}
.pattern-summary-tag.pattern-sev-high { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.pattern-summary-tag.pattern-sev-medium { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.pattern-summary-tag.pattern-sev-low { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.patterns-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 14px;
}
.pattern-card {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-left-width: 4px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 16px;
}
.pattern-card.pattern-sev-high { border-left-color: var(--critical); }
.pattern-card.pattern-sev-medium { border-left-color: var(--high); }
.pattern-card.pattern-sev-low { border-left-color: var(--medium); }
.pattern-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
.pattern-sev-badge {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06);
  color: var(--muted);
}
.pattern-sev-high .pattern-sev-badge { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.pattern-sev-medium .pattern-sev-badge { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.pattern-sev-low .pattern-sev-badge { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.pattern-desc { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; color: #1e293b; margin: 0 0 10px; }
.pattern-evidence { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
.pattern-evidence-pill {
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--muted);
  background: #f8fafc;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
}
.narrative { background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f0f9ff 0%, #ffffff 100%); border: 1px solid #bae6fd; border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px 28px; margin-bottom: 32px; }
.narrative .eyebrow { color: var(--accent); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.narrative .headline { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4; margin: 0 0 14px; color: var(--fg); }
.narrative .body { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: #1e293b; }
.narrative .body p { margin: 0 0 10px; }
.narrative .footer-meta { margin-top: 14px; padding-top: 12px; border-top: 1px solid #e0f2fe; color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; }
.rationale { display: block; margin-top: 4px; color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 12px; }
.trend-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
.trend-bar { flex: 1; height: 6px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 3px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 200px; }
.trend-bar-fill { height: 100%; }
.trend-delta { font-weight: 600; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.delta-up { color: var(--healthy); }
.delta-down { color: var(--critical); }
.delta-flat { color: var(--muted); }
.mermaid-wrap {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 16px;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.mermaid { font-size: 13px; }
.departure-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
.departure-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
.departure-who { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 14px; }
.departure-stats { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 10px; }
.departure-stat .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
.departure-stat .value { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.departure-stat .value.v-crit { color: var(--critical); }
.departure-services .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.departure-services ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; font-size: 13px; }
.departure-card-multi { grid-column: 1 / -1; border-color: var(--accent); border-width: 2px; }
.departure-people { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
.departure-pill { background: #eef2ff; color: #4338ca; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; }
.muted-suffix { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 400; font-size: 12px; margin-left: 4px; }
.resilience-solo { display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: stretch; }
.key-signals { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
.key-signal {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-left-width: 4px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 14px 16px;
}
.key-signal.ks-healthy { border-left-color: var(--healthy); }
.key-signal.ks-risk { border-left-color: var(--high); }
.key-signal .ks-head { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.key-signal .ks-name { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--muted); }
.key-signal .ks-grade {
  font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; padding: 0 8px; border-radius: 4px;
  background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.05);
}
.key-signal .ks-grade-a { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.key-signal .ks-grade-b { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.key-signal .ks-grade-c { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.key-signal .ks-grade-d { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.key-signal .ks-grade-f { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.key-signal .ks-headline { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4; margin-bottom: 6px; color: var(--fg); }
.key-signal .ks-meaning { font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--muted); }
.pattern-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; background: #eef2ff; color: #4338ca; margin-right: 6px; }
.confidence-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
.confidence-badge.confidence-high { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.confidence-badge.confidence-medium { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.confidence-badge.confidence-low { background: #f1f5f9; color: var(--muted); }
.upgrade-hint { margin-top: 14px; padding: 10px 14px; background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04); border-left: 3px solid var(--muted); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted); }
.upgrade-hint strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
.upgrade-hint code { background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; color: var(--fg); }
.upgrade-hint pre { background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06); padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; margin: 6px 0; overflow-x: auto; color: var(--fg); font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
.notice-box { background: #fff7ed; border: 1px solid #fed7aa; border-left: 3px solid var(--high); border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px 16px; color: #7c2d12; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; }
.notice-box strong { color: #7c2d12; }
.notice-box code { background: rgba(124, 45, 18, 0.08); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
.notice-box pre { background: rgba(124, 45, 18, 0.08); padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; margin: 6px 0; overflow-x: auto; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; color: #7c2d12; }
details.architecture-details { margin-top: 24px; }
details.architecture-details summary {
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--muted);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  padding-bottom: 8px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
details.architecture-details[open] summary { color: var(--accent); }
details.signal-detail {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}
details.signal-detail > summary {
  cursor: pointer;
  list-style: none;
  padding: 14px 18px;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--fg);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
}
details.signal-detail > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
details.signal-detail > summary::before {
  content: "▸";
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 12px;
}
details.signal-detail[open] > summary::before { content: "▾"; }
details.signal-detail[open] > summary { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
details.signal-detail > summary .sd-tag {
  margin-left: auto;
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
details.signal-detail > summary .sd-tag.sd-risk { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
details.signal-detail > summary .sd-tag.sd-ok { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.signal-detail-body { padding: 16px 18px 4px; }
.signal-detail-body table { margin-bottom: 8px; }
.signal-detail-body .note:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
</style>
{% if ctx.detailed and ((ctx.module_graph and ctx.module_graph.edges) or (ctx.knowledge_graph and ctx.knowledge_graph.edges)) %}
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@10/dist/mermaid.min.js"></script>
<script>mermaid.initialize({startOnLoad: true, theme: 'neutral', flowchart: {curve: 'basis'}});</script>
{% endif %}
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

<header>
  <h1>blindspot</h1>
  <p class="tagline">Knowledge resilience report</p>
  <p class="meta">
    Repository: <code>{{ ctx.repo_path }}</code><br>
    Generated {{ ctx.generated_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M %Z") }} ·
    window: last {{ ctx.since_days }} days ·
    blindspot v{{ ctx.blindspot_version }}
  </p>
</header>

{% if ctx.top_risks or ctx.business_implication %}
<section class="executive-brief">
  <div class="eyebrow">Executive brief</div>
  {% if ctx.resilience %}
  {% set band_class = "band-" ~ ctx.resilience.band | lower %}
  <p class="overall-line">
    <span class="overall-tag {{ band_class }}">{{ ctx.resilience.band }}</span>
    <span class="overall-text">
      Resilience {{ ctx.resilience.overall }}/100 · {{ ctx.resilience.overall_grade }}
      {% if ctx.repo_profile %}· {{ ctx.repo_profile.replace("-", " ") }} profile{% endif %}
    </span>
  </p>
  {% endif %}
  {% if ctx.top_risks %}
  <div class="risk-list">
    <div class="risk-list-title">Top {{ ctx.top_risks | length }} risk{% if ctx.top_risks | length != 1 %}s{% endif %}</div>
    <ol>
      {% for r in ctx.top_risks %}
        {% set prio_color = ({"High": "critical", "Medium": "high", "Low": "medium"})[r.priority.value] %}
        <li>
          <span class="risk-prio badge {{ prio_color }}">{{ r.priority.value | upper }}</span>
          <strong>{{ r.title }}</strong>
          <span class="risk-target">— <code>{{ r.target }}</code></span>
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
  {% endif %}
  {% if ctx.patterns %}
  <p class="patterns-summary">
    <span class="bi-eyebrow">Patterns detected</span>
    {% for p in ctx.patterns %}
      <span class="pattern-summary-tag pattern-sev-{{ p.severity.value | lower }}">{{ p.name }}</span>
    {% endfor %}
  </p>
  {% endif %}
  {% if ctx.business_implication %}
  <p class="business-implication">
    <span class="bi-eyebrow">Business implication</span>
    {{ ctx.business_implication }}
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.patterns and ctx.detailed %}
<section>
  <h2>Patterns detected</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Composite recognitions — when several single-metric signals fire on
    the same shape, a named pattern names the underlying organisational
    risk. Different from any single recommendation; addresses the
    pattern, not the symptom.
  </p>
  <div class="patterns-grid">
    {% for p in ctx.patterns %}
    <div class="pattern-card pattern-sev-{{ p.severity.value | lower }}">
      <div class="pattern-head">
        <span class="pattern-sev-badge">{{ p.severity.value | upper }}</span>
        <strong>{{ p.name }}</strong>
      </div>
      <p class="pattern-desc">{{ p.description }}</p>
      {% if p.evidence %}
      <div class="pattern-evidence">
        {% for k, v in p.evidence.items() %}
          <span class="pattern-evidence-pill">{{ k.replace("_", " ") }}: {{ v }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.narrative %}
<div class="narrative">
  <div class="eyebrow">Executive summary</div>
  <p class="headline">{{ ctx.narrative.headline_action }}</p>
  <div class="body">
    {% for para in ctx.narrative.executive_summary.split("\n\n") %}
      {% if para.strip() %}<p>{{ para.strip() }}</p>{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="footer-meta">
    Generated by {{ ctx.narrative.model or "LLM" }} · language: {{ ctx.narrative.language }} ·
    treat as advisory, verify against the data below.
  </p>
  {% if ctx.narrative.model == "rule-based" %}
  <div class="upgrade-hint">
    💡 <strong>Want a richer, prose-style executive summary?</strong>
    Add a cloud LLM key (Anthropic or OpenAI) to your scan:
    <pre>--api-key sk-ant-... --provider anthropic --model claude-sonnet-4-6</pre>
    or set <code>narrative.api_key</code> in <code>.blindspot.yaml</code>.
    Without a key, this rule-based narrator is used — deterministic,
    in-process, no network.
  </div>
  {% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}

<h1 class="group-title">Overview</h1>

{% if ctx.resilience %}
{% set band_class = "band-" ~ ctx.resilience.band | lower %}
<section>
  <h2>Engineering Resilience Score</h2>
  <div class="resilience resilience-solo">
    <div class="overall">
      <div class="label">Overall</div>
      <div class="score {{ band_class }}">{{ ctx.resilience.overall }}<span style="font-size:22px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:500;">/100</span> <span class="letter-grade {{ band_class }}" title="Letter grade for the overall score">{{ ctx.resilience.overall_grade }}</span></div>
      <div class="band {{ band_class }}">{{ ctx.resilience.band }}</div>
    </div>
    <p class="summary" style="margin:0;align-self:center;">{{ ctx.resilience.summary }}</p>
  </div>
  {% if ctx.repo_profile %}
  {% set profile_label = ({
    "single-maintainer": "Single-maintainer",
    "founder-led": "Founder-led",
    "team": "Team-based",
    "multi-org": "Multi-org / enterprise",
    "doc-only": "Doc-only",
    "unknown": "Unknown profile",
  }).get(ctx.repo_profile, ctx.repo_profile) %}
  {% set profile_note = ({
    "single-maintainer": "Concentration is structural and expected.",
    "founder-led": "One contributor dominates by design; concentration is structural.",
    "team": "Multiple maintainers without a single dominant contributor.",
    "multi-org": "Concentration signals here are real risks, not artefacts.",
    "doc-only": "Very little code surface — treat results with caution.",
    "unknown": "Mixed signals; profile could not be confidently classified.",
  }).get(ctx.repo_profile, "") %}
  <p class="profile-tag">
    <span class="profile-badge profile-{{ ctx.repo_profile }}">{{ profile_label }}</span>
    <span class="profile-note">{{ profile_note }}</span>
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.key_signals %}
<section>
  <h2>Key signals — the six questions</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Six concrete questions, each with a one-number answer. This is the
    report. Each signal opens up below into the files, services and people
    behind its number — run with <code>--detailed</code> for the
    architecture deep-dive.
  </p>
  <div class="key-signals">
    {% for sig in ctx.key_signals %}
    <div class="key-signal {% if sig.healthy %}ks-healthy{% else %}ks-risk{% endif %}">
      <div class="ks-head">
        <span class="ks-name">{{ sig.name }}</span>
        {% if sig.grade %}<span class="ks-grade ks-grade-{{ sig.grade | lower }}">{{ sig.grade }}</span>{% endif %}
      </div>
      <div class="ks-headline">{{ sig.headline }}</div>
      <div class="ks-meaning">{{ sig.meaning }}</div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.recommendations %}
<section>
  <h2>Recommended actions</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Concrete next steps derived from the signals in this report.
    Each action is tied to a specific finding — treat them as conversation starters
    with the team, not directives.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>Priority</th>
      <th>Confidence</th>
      <th>Category</th>
      <th>Title</th>
      <th>Target</th>
      <th>Evidence</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for a in ctx.recommendations %}
      <tr>
        <td>
          {% set prio_color = ({"High": "critical", "Medium": "high", "Low": "medium"})[a.priority.value] %}
          <span class="badge {{ prio_color }}">{{ a.priority.value }}</span>
        </td>
        <td>
          {% set conf_class = a.confidence.value | lower %}
          <span class="confidence-badge confidence-{{ conf_class }}" title="How much signal density this recommendation rests on">{{ a.confidence.value }}</span>
        </td>
        <td>{{ a.category.value }}</td>
        <td>
          {% if a.pattern %}
          <span class="pattern-badge" title="Recurring fragility pattern">{{ a.pattern.value }}</span>
          {% endif %}
          <strong>{{ a.title }}</strong>
          <div style="margin-top:4px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;">{{ a.description }}</div>
          {% if ctx.narrative and ctx.narrative.rationales.get(a.target) %}
          <span class="rationale">▸ {{ ctx.narrative.rationales[a.target] }}</span>
          {% endif %}
        </td>
        <td><code class="path">{{ a.target }}</code></td>
        <td style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);font-family:ui-monospace,monospace;">{{ a.evidence }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.trend and ctx.trend.snapshots and ctx.detailed %}
<section>
  <h2>Resilience trend</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Historical snapshots based on ownership + decay (review sub-score
    only applies to the present). Use this to see whether resilience is trending up
    or down over the window.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>As of</th>
      <th class="num">Overall</th>
      <th class="num">Ownership</th>
      <th class="num">Decay</th>
      <th>Band</th>
      <th></th>
      {% if ctx.timeline_events %}<th>Event</th>{% endif %}
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for snap in ctx.trend.snapshots %}
      {% set band_lc = snap.score.band | lower %}
      {% set event = ctx.trend_snapshot_events[loop.index0] if ctx.trend_snapshot_events else None %}
      <tr>
        <td>{% if snap.days_ago == 0 %}now{% else %}{{ snap.days_ago }} days ago{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num band-{{ band_lc }}" style="font-weight:600;">{{ snap.score.overall }}</td>
        <td class="num">{% if snap.score.ownership is not none %}{{ snap.score.ownership }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num">{% if snap.score.decay is not none %}{{ snap.score.decay }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {% if snap.score.band == 'Strong' %}healthy{% elif snap.score.band == 'Moderate' %}medium{% elif snap.score.band == 'Fragile' %}high{% else %}critical{% endif %}">{{ snap.score.band }}</span></td>
        <td>
          <div class="trend-bar">
            <div class="trend-bar-fill band-{{ band_lc }}" style="width: {{ snap.score.overall }}%; background: currentColor;"></div>
          </div>
        </td>
        {% if ctx.timeline_events %}
        <td style="font-size:12px;">
          {% if event %}
          <span class="event-marker" title="{{ event.date }}">⚑ {{ event.label }}</span>
          {% else %}—{% endif %}
        </td>
        {% endif %}
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% if ctx.trend.delta_overall is not none %}
  <p class="summary" style="margin-top:12px;">
    Change vs oldest snapshot:
    {% if ctx.trend.delta_overall > 0 %}
      <span class="trend-delta delta-up">▲ +{{ ctx.trend.delta_overall }}</span> — improving.
    {% elif ctx.trend.delta_overall < 0 %}
      <span class="trend-delta delta-down">▼ {{ ctx.trend.delta_overall }}</span> — declining.
    {% else %}
      <span class="trend-delta delta-flat">— flat</span>.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.key_signals %}
<h1 class="group-title">Signal details</h1>
<p class="note">
  Each signal above, opened up — the files, services and people behind the
  headline number. Risk signals are expanded by default; healthy ones stay
  collapsed.
</p>

{# 1 — Ownership concentration #}
<details class="signal-detail"{% if not ctx.key_signals[0].healthy %} open{% endif %}>
  <summary>Ownership concentration — service risk map
    <span class="sd-tag {% if ctx.key_signals[0].healthy %}sd-ok{% else %}sd-risk{% endif %}">{% if ctx.key_signals[0].healthy %}healthy{% else %}risk{% endif %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="signal-detail-body">
    <p class="note">
      Bus factor measures how many people would need to leave before
      knowledge of a service is critically lost. A bus factor of 1 means a
      single person carries the service.
    </p>
    {% if ctx.services %}
    <table>
      <thead><tr>
        <th>Service</th><th class="num">Files</th><th class="num">Bus factor</th>
        <th>Risk</th><th>Top owner</th><th class="num">Their coverage</th>
      </tr></thead>
      <tbody>
      {% for s in ctx.services %}
        <tr>
          <td><code>{{ s.service }}</code></td>
          <td class="num">{{ s.file_count }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ s.bus_factor }}</td>
          <td><span class="badge {{ s.risk_level }}">{{ s.risk_level }}</span></td>
          <td>{% if s.top_owners %}{{ ctx.label(s.top_owners[0][0]) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
          <td class="num">{% if s.top_owners %}{{ s.top_owners[0][1] | pct }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        </tr>
      {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% else %}
    <div class="empty">No services analyzed in this window.</div>
    {% endif %}
    {% if ctx.critical_files %}
    <h3 style="margin-top:20px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#475569;">Files with single ownership</h3>
    <p class="note">Entirely owned by one person — the most acute knowledge risk.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Owner</th><th class="num">Coverage</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
      {% for f in ctx.critical_files %}
        <tr>
          <td><code class="path">{{ f.file }}</code></td>
          <td>{{ ctx.label(f.top_owners[0][0]) }}</td>
          <td class="num"><span class="badge critical">{{ f.top_owners[0][1] | pct }}</span></td>
        </tr>
      {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</details>

{# 2 — Single-engineer dependency #}
<details class="signal-detail"{% if not ctx.key_signals[1].healthy %} open{% endif %}>
  <summary>Single-engineer dependency — departure scenarios
    <span class="sd-tag {% if ctx.key_signals[1].healthy %}sd-ok{% else %}sd-risk{% endif %}">{% if ctx.key_signals[1].healthy %}healthy{% else %}risk{% endif %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="signal-detail-body">
  {% if ctx.departure_scenarios %}
  <p class="note">
    For each of the top contributors by aggregate ownership coverage, this
    is what would happen if they left tomorrow: how many files lose their
    primary expert, how many become unowned (orphan, top remaining
    coverage &lt; 30%), and which services take the largest hit. Use this
    to prioritise pair-work and knowledge transfer.
  </p>
  <div class="departure-grid">
    {% for scenario in ctx.departure_scenarios %}
    {% set svc_top = scenario.services[:3] %}
    {% set orphan_pct = (scenario.orphaned_files / scenario.total_files) if scenario.total_files else 0 %}
    {% set sev = "critical" if scenario.orphaned_files > 0 else ("high" if scenario.avg_coverage_loss > 0.30 else "medium") %}
    {% set is_multi = scenario.departing | length > 1 %}
    <div class="departure-card{% if is_multi %} departure-card-multi{% endif %}">
      <div class="departure-who">
        <span class="badge {{ sev }}">{{ sev | upper }}</span>
        {% if is_multi %}
        <strong>If {{ scenario.departing | length }} people leave together</strong>
        {% else %}
        <strong>If {{ ctx.label(scenario.departing[0]) }} leaves</strong>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      {% if is_multi %}
      <div class="departure-people">
        {% for email in scenario.departing %}
          <span class="departure-pill">{{ ctx.label(email) }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="departure-stats">
        <div class="departure-stat">
          <div class="label">Files affected</div>
          <div class="value">{{ scenario.affected_files }}<span class="muted-suffix"> / {{ scenario.total_files }}</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="departure-stat">
          <div class="label">Orphan files</div>
          <div class="value{% if scenario.orphaned_files %} v-crit{% endif %}">{{ scenario.orphaned_files }}<span class="muted-suffix"> ({{ orphan_pct | pct }})</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="departure-stat">
          <div class="label">Avg coverage loss</div>
          <div class="value">{{ scenario.avg_coverage_loss | pct }}</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% if svc_top %}
      <div class="departure-services">
        <div class="label">Most-affected services</div>
        <ul>
        {% for s in svc_top %}
          <li>
            <code class="path">{{ s.service }}</code>
            <span class="muted-suffix">{{ s.affected_files }}/{{ s.file_count }} files
              {%- if s.orphaned_files %}, {{ s.orphaned_files }} orphan{%- endif -%}
              , {{ s.avg_coverage_loss | pct }} avg loss</span>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No contributor's departure orphans critical files.</div>
  {% endif %}
  </div>
</details>

{# 3 — Knowledge decay #}
<details class="signal-detail"{% if not ctx.key_signals[2].healthy %} open{% endif %}>
  <summary>Knowledge decay — top concerns
    <span class="sd-tag {% if ctx.key_signals[2].healthy %}sd-ok{% else %}sd-risk{% endif %}">{% if ctx.key_signals[2].healthy %}healthy{% else %}risk{% endif %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="signal-detail-body">
  <p class="note">
    Decay rises when an owner stops touching a file and others have been changing it.
    The 90-day projection shows the trajectory if nothing changes.
  </p>
  {% if ctx.decay_top %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th><th>Top owner</th>
      <th class="num">Days since touch</th>
      <th class="num">Decay score</th>
      <th>Risk</th>
      <th class="num">90-day projection</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for d in ctx.decay_top %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ d.file }}</code></td>
        <td>{{ ctx.label(d.top_owner) }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ d.days_since_owner_touch | days }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ d.decay_score | pct }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {{ d.risk_level }}">{{ d.risk_level }}</span></td>
        <td class="num">{{ d.projections[90] | pct }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No file is critically decayed.</div>
  {% endif %}
  </div>
</details>

{# 4 — Review depth #}
<details class="signal-detail"{% if not ctx.key_signals[3].healthy %} open{% endif %}>
  <summary>Review depth — review lineage
    <span class="sd-tag {% if ctx.key_signals[3].healthy %}sd-ok{% else %}sd-risk{% endif %}">{% if ctx.key_signals[3].healthy %}healthy{% else %}risk{% endif %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="signal-detail-body">
  {% if ctx.reviews_enabled %}
  <p class="note">
    Review data fetched from GitHub ({{ ctx.pr_count }} PRs analyzed{% if ctx.pr_truncated %}, partial — rate limit hit{% endif %}).
    A rubber-stamp ratio is the share of approvals on a file that arrived without a single review comment.
    Reviewer diversity measures whether several people share the review load.
  </p>
  <h3 style="margin-top:16px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#475569;">Files with highest rubber-stamp ratio</h3>
  {% if ctx.top_rubber_stamps %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Reviewers</th>
      <th class="num">Reviews</th>
      <th class="num">Comments</th>
      <th class="num">Rubber-stamp</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in ctx.top_rubber_stamps %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ s.file }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.unique_reviewers }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.total_reviews }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.total_comments }}</td>
        <td class="num"><span class="badge {% if s.rubber_stamp_ratio >= 0.8 %}critical{% elif s.rubber_stamp_ratio >= 0.5 %}high{% else %}medium{% endif %}">{{ s.rubber_stamp_ratio | pct }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No rubber-stamp patterns detected.</div>
  {% endif %}
  <h3 style="margin-top:20px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#475569;">Files with lowest reviewer diversity</h3>
  {% if ctx.low_diversity_files %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Reviewers</th>
      <th class="num">Reviews</th>
      <th class="num">Diversity</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in ctx.low_diversity_files %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ s.file }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.unique_reviewers }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.total_reviews }}</td>
        <td class="num"><span class="badge {% if s.diversity_hhi < 0.2 %}critical{% elif s.diversity_hhi < 0.5 %}high{% else %}medium{% endif %}">{{ s.diversity_hhi | pct }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No low-diversity files detected.</div>
  {% endif %}
  {% elif ctx.detected_remote %}
  <div class="notice-box">
    🔌 <strong>Review metrics unavailable for this scan.</strong>
    {% if ctx.detected_remote == "github" %}
    A GitHub remote was detected, but no credentials were available.
    Enable it once and re-run the scan to unlock rubber-stamp ratio,
    reviewer diversity, fast-approval detection, and the PR activity mix:
    <pre>gh auth login                          # uses gh CLI (recommended)</pre>
    or pass a token directly:
    <pre>--github-token ghp_...</pre>
    or add it to <code>.blindspot.yaml</code>:
    <pre>github:
  token: ghp_...</pre>
    {% elif ctx.detected_remote == "bitbucket" %}
    A Bitbucket Cloud remote was detected, but no credentials were
    configured. Bitbucket Cloud has no anonymous access, so review
    metrics need an Atlassian API token (or legacy app password):
    <pre>--bitbucket-username you@email.com --bitbucket-app-password ATATT3...</pre>
    or add a block to <code>.blindspot.yaml</code>:
    <pre>bitbucket:
  username: you@email.com
  app_password: ATATT3...</pre>
    Create the token at <code>id.atlassian.com → API tokens</code> with
    <code>read:pullrequest:bitbucket</code> + <code>read:repository:bitbucket</code> scopes.
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No remote detected — review depth needs a GitHub or Bitbucket remote.</div>
  {% endif %}
  </div>
</details>

{# 5 — Correction load #}
<details class="signal-detail"{% if not ctx.key_signals[4].healthy %} open{% endif %}>
  <summary>Correction load — files with a bugfix tail
    <span class="sd-tag {% if ctx.key_signals[4].healthy %}sd-ok{% else %}sd-risk{% endif %}">{% if ctx.key_signals[4].healthy %}healthy{% else %}risk{% endif %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="signal-detail-body">
  {% if ctx.correction_load_files %}
  <p class="note">
    Share of recent commits to each file that are follow-up fixes or reverts.
    A high ratio is observable evidence of <em>stability debt</em> — work is
    shipping but corrections are paying for it. Look at the surface, not the
    person.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Total commits</th>
      <th class="num">Fixes</th>
      <th class="num">Reverts</th>
      <th class="num">Correction ratio</th>
      <th>Risk</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for f in ctx.correction_load_files[:15] %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ f.file }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.total_commits }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.fix_commits }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.revert_commits }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.correction_ratio | pct }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {{ f.risk_level }}">{{ f.risk_level }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No correction-load data for this window.</div>
  {% endif %}
  </div>
</details>

{# 6 — AI-readable context #}
<details class="signal-detail"{% if not ctx.key_signals[5].healthy %} open{% endif %}>
  <summary>AI-readable context — operational docs coverage
    <span class="sd-tag {% if ctx.key_signals[5].healthy %}sd-ok{% else %}sd-risk{% endif %}">{% if ctx.key_signals[5].healthy %}healthy{% else %}risk{% endif %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="signal-detail-body">
  {% if ctx.ai_readiness %}
  <p class="note">
    Coverage of AI-readable organizational memory — agent rules, specs,
    prompts, architecture decisions, skills. The repo-root row is what the
    signal grades; per-service rows are shown for context. This is not an
    AI-generated-code detector.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>Surface</th>
      <th>Agent rules</th>
      <th>Specs</th>
      <th>Prompts</th>
      <th>Architecture</th>
      <th>Skills</th>
      <th class="num">Coverage</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% set rows = [ctx.ai_readiness.repo] + (ctx.ai_readiness.services | list)[:10] %}
      {% for r in rows %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ r.target }}</td>
        <td>{% if r.agent_rules %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.specs %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.prompts %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.architecture %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.skills %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ (r.coverage_ratio * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No file structure to assess AI-readable context.</div>
  {% endif %}
  </div>
</details>
{% endif %}{# end ctx.key_signals #}

{% if ctx.detailed %}
<h1 class="group-title">Architecture &amp; deep-dive</h1>

{% if ctx.knowledge_graph and ctx.knowledge_graph.edges %}
<section>
  <h2>Knowledge graph — who carries what</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Top contributors × top services, edges only where one person carries
    ≥ 10% of a service's effective ownership. Thick edges = single-owner
    concentration. <strong>Read it as:</strong> the team-shaped picture
    of where knowledge lives.
  </p>
  <div class="mermaid-wrap">
    <pre class="mermaid">
graph LR
{% for c in ctx.knowledge_graph.contributors -%}
  c_{{ loop.index }}["{{ ctx.label(c) }}"]:::contributor
{% endfor -%}
{% for s in ctx.knowledge_graph.services -%}
  s_{{ loop.index }}["{{ s }}"]:::service
{% endfor -%}
{% for e in ctx.knowledge_graph.edges -%}
  {% set ci = ctx.knowledge_graph.contributors.index(e.contributor) + 1 -%}
  {% set si = ctx.knowledge_graph.services.index(e.service) + 1 -%}
  c_{{ ci }} -->|"{{ (e.coverage * 100) | round(0) | int }}%"| s_{{ si }}
{% endfor -%}
classDef contributor fill:#eef2ff,stroke:#4338ca,stroke-width:1px,color:#1e1b4b;
classDef service fill:#f0fdf4,stroke:#16a34a,stroke-width:1px,color:#14532d;
    </pre>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.change_fear and ctx.change_fear.files %}
<section>
  <h2>Change-fear index — files nobody dares to touch</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Structurally central files (high PageRank) edited by very few people
    and untouched recently. The team is shipping around them. <strong>Read it as:</strong>
    if one of these breaks, the muscle memory is gone — and so is whoever wrote it.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Importance</th>
      <th class="num">Contributors</th>
      <th class="num">Days since touch</th>
      <th>Risk</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for f in ctx.change_fear.files %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ f.file }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ (f.importance * 100) | round(2) }}%</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.contributor_count }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.days_since_touch | round(0) | int }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {{ f.risk_level }}">{{ f.risk_level }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.module_graph and ctx.module_graph.edges %}
<details class="architecture-details">
  <summary>Module dependency map</summary>
  <section style="margin-top:16px;">
    <p class="note">
      Top-level directories rolled up from the file dependency graph. Each
      node is a module ({{ ctx.module_graph.nodes | length }} shown, ranked by
      total connection weight); each edge is the count of file-level imports
      crossing between them. Arrows point from caller to callee.
    </p>
    <div class="mermaid-wrap">
      <pre class="mermaid">
graph LR
{% for n in ctx.module_graph.nodes -%}
  m_{{ n.name | replace('/', '_') | replace('-', '_') | replace('.', '_') | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') }}["{{ n.name }}<br/>{{ n.file_count }} file{% if n.file_count != 1 %}s{% endif %}"]
{% endfor -%}
{% for e in ctx.module_graph.edges -%}
  m_{{ e.from_module | replace('/', '_') | replace('-', '_') | replace('.', '_') | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') }} -->|{{ e.weight }}| m_{{ e.to_module | replace('/', '_') | replace('-', '_') | replace('.', '_') | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') }}
{% endfor -%}
      </pre>
    </div>
  </section>
</details>
{% endif %}
{% endif %}{# end ctx.detailed #}

<footer>
  <p><strong>Methodology.</strong>
    Ownership is scored from commit count, change volume, recency, and review depth (review data pending).
    Decay combines code volatility since the owner's last touch with their absence over time.
    All metrics are evidence-derived; treat them as inputs to a conversation, not verdicts.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Privacy.</strong>
    Service-level views are the default. Individual data is shown only in service context and is
    intended for knowledge planning, not performance evaluation.
  </p>
  <p>blindspot v{{ ctx.blindspot_version }} · pre-alpha</p>
</footer>

</div>
</body>
</html>
